						               													<description>Description from the designer:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Project Spera is a cooperative 2 - 4 player survival horror game inspired by games like the original Resident Evil and Silent Hill, that uses deck building, tile exploration, and variable player powers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The year is 2136.  For centuries now the world has been overrun with monsters, demons, and any other number of unspeakable horrors.  A team of scientists and historians have traced everything back to a single cataclysmic event in a war torn 1940's, when the axis powers tore a hole in the fabric of reality.&amp;#10;Humanity is on the verge of extinction, and Project Spera, is its last hope...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Project Spera, players take on the role of a team of people salvaging the remains of a device that was once meant to save the world. Players will need to explore a hidden facility, arm themselves with what limited resources they can afford, and work together to defeat the creatures within.  The game is won when the final boss is defeated, and the cataclysm is averted.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You are all alone, your resources limited, and the horrors within leave you on the edge of insanity.  Will you survive?  Or will you succumb to the darkness&amp;hellip;and be lost&amp;hellip;forever?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
